main event: A flying saucer was reported over northern Norway by observers and tracked on radar on March 19, 1958.
interesting points: The object was described as elliptical in shape,The sighting involved multiple witnesses,It emitted a humming or whistling sound as it passed,No planes were reported in the area at the time of the sighting,The sighting was confirmed by preliminary and follow-up investigations by the Norwegian Air Force.
witness description: Norwegian Air Force officers and other observers in the area
